Morphological variation
. Fore wing 8.0– 
13.6 mm
. Ovipositor 1.14–1.28 length of hind tibia. Mandible ventral tooth almost twice as long as dorsal tooth. Antenna with 25–26 flagellomeres, white band with 9–13, starting at flagellomere IV at apical 0.3–0.6. Color: clypeal sulcus entirely yellow; supraclypeal area rarely centrally black (1/ 
16 females
). Mesoscutum centrally with large yellow spot (8/ 
16 females
); fore coxa mesally or postero-basally, brown; mid coxa mostly yellowish brown, basally with large pale yellow spot; hind coxa dorso-basally with large yellow spot; hind t5 entirely reddish brown. Metasoma: T1 often (8/ 
16 females
) centrally light orange instead of black.

MALE. Very similar to female, except as follows. Antenna with 27–28 flagellomeres; white band with 6, starting at flagellomere X at apical 0.5; smallest specimens white band with 4 articles, starting at flagellomere XI. Propodeal sculpturing behind posterior transverse carina finely and irregularly rugulose. Color: mesoscutum always with central yellow spot; fore and mid legs color generally much lighter than on female, without orange tones; hind coxa to tibia deep yellow, on smallest specimen yellowish brown, tibia darkened at apex; at least some of t1–4 on any leg white; metasoma with varied striped patterns of black, yellow and light orange (
Figs 91, 92, 93
).
